  "prompt": "When entering the US will I be detained for a bench warrant?",
  "response": "If you have an outstanding bench warrant when entering the United States, there is a possibility that you could be detained upon your arrival. A bench warrant is typically issued by a judge when someone fails to appear in court or violates a court order. \n\nWhen you enter the U.S., the Customs and Border Protection (CBP) officers may run your information through various databases, and if the warrant appears in those records, they may take you into custody. It's important to consult with a legal professional or an immigration attorney to understand your situation better and explore your options before traveling.",
